        <h3 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold">Kilimani Primary School</h3>
        <p>
          BASIK began life in 2006 when we started raising money to fund the
          rebuilding of Kilimani Primary School.
        </p>

        <p>
          The school was a mud hut in a rural location outside Mombasa, with
          two teachers supporting 70 students. It had no basic facilities
          and materials. We worked with Head Teacher Julius Nzai to rebuild
          the school and support children who couldn't afford to pay their
          fees to get an education.
        </p>

        <p>
          Kilimani now has brick built classrooms for all year groups, a
          staff room, toilets, clean running water and more teachers to
          provide a better quality education. The school now supports over
          150 students from the local community! This was our first project
          as a charity and we're very proud of what we helped to achieve at
          Kilimani and the opportunities the students will gain from an
          education.
        </p>
